      },
      "writtenOn": "2015-11-24T23:51:08Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This is not guaranteed to be the latest version.\nIn fact, QDir::entryList() is not guaranteed to return items in any particular order, unless sorting is specified (in this case, it isn\u0027t).\nBut even if it was sorted alphabetically, how do we know that the alphabetically last folder is actually the latest version?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 223,
        "startChar": 33,
        "endLine": 223,
        "endChar": 37
      },
      "revId": "a7c448a3faed6e4da66aa1c313e4be95f9c73d40",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "9bf043de_70985038",
        "filename": "android/skin/qt/tool-window.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 223,
      "author": {
        "id": 1079203
      },
      "writtenOn": "2015-11-30T18:23:51Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I wasn\u0027t sure about the best way to find the latest version: see http://tools.android.com/tech-docs/configuration\n\nListing them alphabetically and picking the last one *should* always pick the latest full version of Android Studio, but this won\u0027t take into account Preview releases. Suggestions?",
      "parentUuid": "fbb05f0b_d0c6ea1c",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 223,
        "startChar": 33,
        "endLine": 223,
        "endChar": 37
      },
      "revId": "a7c448a3faed6e4da66aa1c313e4be95f9c73d40",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "db0f1bb0_2aafffe9",
        "filename": "android/skin/qt/tool-window.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 223,
      "author": {
        "id": 1078773
      },
      "writtenOn": "2015-11-30T18:39:12Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Consider this possibility: you have versions 1.1, 1.12 and 1.3. Technically 1.3 should be before 1.12 (since 3 \u003c 12) but when sorted alphabetically I think 1.12 will come before 1.3.\n\nThe link you posted is pretty specific about the format of the names, so I think it would be safe to actually parse the filtered names, sort them (numerically) by version and pick the latest one.\n\nI am not sure what to do with preview SDKs- is it ok to initialize SDK path to a preview version if it happens to be the latest? If yes, then we don\u0027t need to do any additional checks, otherwise we need to ensure that we\u0027re initializing to the latest *stable* version and only fall back on preview if there are no stable versions available.",
      "parentUuid": "9bf043de_70985038",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 223,
        "startChar": 33,
        "endLine": 223,
        "endChar": 37
      },
      "revId": "a7c448a3faed6e4da66aa1c313e4be95f9c73d40",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
